¦ The Measure class is the base class of every measure class.
¦ A measure class is a class which represents a real-life measure with a value and a unit.
¦ Internally, the value of a measure uses double-precision floating point.
¦ @author Vincent Philippe (@vincent64)
¦ @version v0.5
class+ Measure {
    ~ const double value;

    ¦ Constructs a measure with the given value.
    ¦ @param value the value
    fn~ constructor(attr double value) { }

    ¦ Returns the measure value in the default unit.
    ¦ @returns the measure value
    fn+ double value() = value;
}